rs are a rare breed in a field that is otherwise seen as dirty work and in a system that is overburdened, under-resourced, and overshadowed by social, cultural, and political pressures.Examining the ugliest side of our criminal justice system, Capital Defense offers an up-close perspective on the capital litigation process and its impact on the people who participate in it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aCapital punishmentzUnited States. 0aDefense (Criminal procedure)zUnited States. 4aPTSD. 4aattorney-client relations. 4acapital punishment. 4acause lawyers. 4acommunity of practice. 4acoping strategies. 4acriminal defense. 4acriminal justice system. 4adefense lawyers. 4adiscrimination. 4aemotional work. 4afeminization. 4agendered work. 4aidentity. 4ainsiders versus outsiders. 4aintersectionality. 4alegal profession. 4amitigation investigation. 4amorality. 4asociology of law. 4atrauma. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aBarak, Maya Pagni, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479806973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479806973.jpg  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK